# Qwik web-public surface for `<project-name>`

The public-facing **Qwik City** web surface for `<project-name>`, mirroring the
`full-stack-monorepo` 2.0.0 Qwik shell (B.8.9). It renders a minimal RAG query UI
and talks to the backend through a generated **Connect-ES v2** client.

## Layout

```text
frontend/web-public/
├── package.json            # Qwik + Connect-ES v2 + protobuf-es v2 pins
├── tsconfig.json           # ~/* → ./src/* alias; Bundler resolution
├── vite.config.ts          # qwikCity + qwikVite plugins
├── .nvmrc                  # Node 24
├── qwik.env.d.ts           # Qwik/Vite type references
└── src/
    ├── entry.ssr.tsx       # renderToStream SSR entry
    ├── root.tsx            # QwikCityProvider + RouterOutlet
    ├── routes/index.tsx    # streaming RAG UI (input → QueryStream → progressive answer + Stop/cancel + retry→unary + fallback indicator)
    └── lib/
        ├── connect-client.ts          # Connect-ES v2 client → rag.v1.RagService.Query (unary) + QueryStream (server-streaming)
        └── generated/connect/         # buf-generated rag_pb.ts (materialised by `task proto`)
```

## RAG query UI

`src/routes/index.tsx` ships a minimal, resumable UI: an input box fires a
**server-streaming** `RagService.QueryStream` call via `src/lib/connect-client.ts`,
consumed with `for await` so the answer renders **progressively** (token-by-token,
Article XI.4 — no blocking synchronous AI call). It also renders the grounding
source chunks and a **`fallbackUsed` indicator** that surfaces the Article XI.5
non-AI fallback path (shown when the AI upstream is unavailable or over budget).

### Streaming, cancellation, and graceful degradation (B.7.10)

- **Progressive render** — each `token_delta` frame appends to a Qwik signal as
  it arrives; the one-shot `sources` frame is rendered before the tokens.
- **Stop / cancel** — a Stop control aborts the in-flight stream via an
  `AbortController` whose `signal` is threaded into the Connect call. The stream
  is also cancelled **on unmount** (Qwik `useVisibleTask$` cleanup), so no
  orphaned stream survives navigation away from the route.
- **Exponential-backoff retry → unary degradation** — on transient stream errors
  the UI retries with a named exponential-backoff policy (`DEFAULT_RETRY_POLICY`
  / `exponentialBackoffMs` in `connect-client.ts`); on exhausting the bounded
  attempts it **degrades to the unary `query()`** path — the UI-layer Article
  XI.5 fallback (SSE-class → unary → non-AI fallback answer).

### WebTransport — documented forward alternative (NOT the default)

The **default** streaming transport is **Connect server-streaming** (SSE-class),
because Connect-ES v2 is fetch/HTTP-based and **does not transport over
WebTransport**. WebTransport (HTTP/3 datagrams/streams) is recorded here as a
**forward alternative**, NOT wired in this archetype (ADR-B7-10-005): adopting it
would mean a separate, non-Connect native-browser `WebTransport` client plus a
dedicated backend HTTP/3 endpoint outside the Connect handler — a larger surface
best landed as its own change. Until then, Connect server-streaming over the
existing Envoy ingress is the streaming path; this note is the upgrade marker, not
a scaffolded second transport.

## Connect-ES + proto codegen (run `task proto` first)

`src/lib/connect-client.ts` imports the `RagService` descriptor from
`./generated/connect/rag_pb` — generated by buf (`buf.build/bufbuild/es:v2.2.0`,
`target=ts`) from `shared/protos/v1/rag/rag.proto`. Connect-ES v2 retired the
separate `*_connect` file: the single protobuf-es v2 `*_pb` file carries both the
message types and the service descriptor. **The generated file does not exist
until you run `task proto`** (`cd shared/protos && buf generate`) — a `tsc`/build
will report the missing import until then. This mirrors the flagship 2.0.0
web-public surface, whose Connect client likewise imports a buf-generated
descriptor.

## Scope notes

- **Web-public only** — there is no Flutter mobile app in this archetype
  (`ADR-B7-2-006`). Adopters wanting a mobile surface add it as a separate change.
- **Streaming + unary** — `QueryStream` (server-streaming, SSE-class) is the
  default answer path (B.7.10); the unary `Query` is **retained** as the UI-layer
  XI.5 degradation target (the stream degrades to it on repeated stream errors).
  WebTransport stays a documented forward alternative (above), not the default.

